markets.title: Will a bill that restricts SNAP benefits become law before Jan 4, 2027?
markets.rules_primary: If a bill that restricts SNAP benefits become law before Jan 4, 2027, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: This market will resolve to Yes if a bill that explicitly restricts the types of food that can be purchased using Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits is signed into law by the President on or before January 3, 2027 (the end of the 119th Congress). The bill must clearly impose new federal restrictions on eligible SNAP purchases. Administrative rule changes, state-level restrictions, or temporary pilot programs do not count.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
